This year&rsquo;s national Madaraka day celebrations will be held at the newly built Jomo Kenyatta international stadium in Kisumu. A high-level government delegation led by interior ps Dr Karanja kibicho visited the venue to inspect the ongoing construction works. President Kenyatta will preside over the national celebrations at the facility which is currently being constructed at a cost of 350 million shillings. this is the first time the lakeside city will be hosting the national event. among the leaders accompanying the ps on the inspection tour was Kisumu governor prof peter Anyang nyongo.